(370, 3, 'page', '{\"_token\":\"xfbikW6Je58DGdldu9DGahhEpIUNqmVLuuRhiveJ\",\"name\":\"James Quantrill\",\"slug\":\"james-quantrill\",\"slug_id\":\"0\",\"model\":\"Botble\\\\Page\\\\Models\\\\Page\",\"description\":\"Headteacher\\r\\nPost Graduate Certificate in Education\\r\\nBachelor of Business and Management (Hons)\",\"content\":\"<h1 style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#2980b9;\\\">Our Teachers<\\/span><\\/h1>\\r\\n\\r\\n<article itemscope=\\\"\\\" itemtype=\\\"http:\\/\\/schema.org\\/Article\\\">\\r\\n<header>\\r\\n<h2 itemprop=\\\"name\\\" style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#2980b9;\\\">James Quantrill<\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:center\\\"><img alt=\\\"\\\" height=\\\"400\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/sgstar.edu.vn\\/storage\\/teacher\\/james-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"400\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:14px;\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#2980b9;\\\">Headteacher<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Post Graduate Certificate in Education<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Bachelor of Business and Management (Hons)<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>James attained Qualified Teacher Status from the Chase Lane Primary School Programme in Essex, England. After four years teaching in his initial placement at the very same school, James moved to an &#39;Outstanding&#39; school, Lawford C of E Primary School, where he led the Sports and oversaw the introduction to the new Computing curriculum. James spent three years there, becoming part of the Leadership team and assuming the role of Key Stage 2 Manager in his final year. Seeking new challenges further afield, James joined the Saigon Star family in 2014. James uses his soccer knowledge to good use when coaching the school team but also in his spare time when he plays in the Saigon International Football League. Elsewhere, he also enjoys travelling, adventure sports, tennis and films.<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/header>\\r\\n<\\/article>\",\"is_featured\":\"0\",\"gallery\":null,\"seo_meta\":{\"seo_title\":null,\"seo_description\":null},\"submit\":\"save\",\"language\":\"en_US\",\"ref_from\":null,\"status\":\"published\",\"template\":\"default\",\"image\":\"teacher\\/james-1.jpg\"}', 'created', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/79.0.3945.130 Safari/537.36', '14.241.249.67', 3, 29, 'James Quantrill', 'info', '2020-02-21 02:16:08', '2020-02-21 02:16:08'),
(371, 3, 'page', '{\"_token\":\"xfbikW6Je58DGdldu9DGahhEpIUNqmVLuuRhiveJ\",\"name\":\"Asmaa Hussein\",\"slug\":\"asmaa-hussein\",\"slug_id\":\"0\",\"model\":\"Botble\\\\Page\\\\Models\\\\Page\",\"description\":\"Year 7 Tutor & Assistant Headteacher (Head of Middle Years)\",\"content\":\"<h1 style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#2980b9;\\\">Our Teachers<\\/span><\\/h1>\\r\\n\\r\\n<article itemscope=\\\"\\\" itemtype=\\\"http:\\/\\/schema.org\\/Article\\\">\\r\\n<header>\\r\\n<h2 itemprop=\\\"name\\\" style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#2980b9;\\\">Asmaa Hussein<\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:center\\\"><img alt=\\\"\\\" height=\\\"400\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/sgstar.edu.vn\\/storage\\/teacher\\/assma.jpg\\\" width=\\\"400\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/header>\\r\\n<\\/article>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#2980b9;\\\">Year 7 Tutor &amp; Assistant Headteacher (Head of Middle Years)<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>M.S. Multidisciplinary Studies, concentration in Educational Technology and Information Literacy (in progress), State University of New York, USA.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>New Jersey State Standard Teaching License, K-8 education, specialization in Science, William Paterson University, USA.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>B.S. Finance and Economics (Hons), Rutgers University, USA.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Asmaa was born in New York City and had started out her professional career on Wall Street. However, an opening for a secondary science teacher at a local school helped guide her to discover her true passion, teaching. Before returning to Saigon Star International School this year, Asmaa has enjoyed twelve years of teaching at six different schools in the USA, Egypt, Vietnam, Brazil, and Taiwan. She has served in leadership roles at several of these schools, and has helped to found The American School of Vietnam in 2010 and Asia American International Academy (Taiwan) in 2016. Asmaa believes her job as an educator is to help foster a growth mindset and the development of grit in young people so that they may grow to be successful global citizens. Besides travelling and learning new languages, Asmaa enjoys reading, playing tennis, and outdoor and underwater activities, with a passion for marine conservation.<\\/p>\",\"is_featured\":\"0\",\"gallery\":null,\"seo_meta\":{\"seo_title\":null,\"seo_description\":null},\"submit\":\"save\",\"language\":\"en_US\",\"ref_from\":null,\"status\":\"published\",\"template\":\"default\",\"image\":\"teacher\\/assma.jpg\"}', 'created', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/79.0.3945.130 Safari/537.36', '14.241.249.67', 3, 30, 'Asmaa Hussein', 'info', '2020-02-21 02:19:20', '2020-02-21 02:19:20'),
(372, 3, 'page', '{\"_token\":\"xfbikW6Je58DGdldu9DGahhEpIUNqmVLuuRhiveJ\",\"name\":\"Grace Collantes\",\"slug\":\"grace-collantes\",\"slug_id\":\"0\",\"model\":\"Botble\\\\Page\\\\Models\\\\Page\",\"description\":\"Nursery Class Teacher\\r\\nBachelor of Science - Major in Child Development Education, Miriam College, Philippines\",\"content\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#2980b9;\\\">Our Teachers<br \\/>\\r\\nGrace Collantes<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:center\\\"><img alt=\\\"\\\" height=\\\"400\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/sgstar.edu.vn\\/storage\\/teacher\\/grace-1.jpg\\\" width=\\\"400\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#2980b9;\\\">Nursery Class Teacher<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Bachelor of Science - Major in Child Development Education, Miriam College, Philippines<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This is now Ms. Grace&rsquo;s fifth year at Saigon Star. She is very passionate in early&nbsp;childhood education and the IEYC curriculum. In the past four years, Ms Grace has undertaken several workshops and courses to develop her practice, deepening her decade-long teaching career. Her new role as a Nursery teacher, as well as the Head of Early Years, will truly strengthen a new chapter of opportunities. Ms Grace believes that the triangle of support for children must be equilateral amongst teachers, the school, and their parents. She is looking forward to making a big impact towards a very fruitful year ahead with our school community.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Being a lifelong learner herself, Ms Grace&#39;s teaching practice is inspired by a holistic approach through yoga, mindfulness and environmental protection. When traveling, she enjoys outdoor adventures, such as hiking and scuba diving.&nbsp;Vietnam has been Ms Grace&#39;s second home for the past six years, and she hopes to discover plenty more about Vietnamese culture, food, people and history.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"is_featured\":\"0\",\"gallery\":null,\"seo_meta\":{\"seo_title\":null,\"seo_description\":null},\"submit\":\"save\",\"language\":\"en_US\",\"ref_from\":null,\"status\":\"published\",\"template\":\"default\",\"image\":null}', 'created', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/79.0.3945.130 Safari/537.36', '14.241.249.67', 3, 31, 'Grace Collantes', 'info', '2020-02-21 02:23:26', '2020-02-21 02:23:26'),
