(51, 'Middle Years (age 11-14)', '<header>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"343\" src=\"http://sgstar.edu.vn/storage/middleyears/fun04.jpg\" width=\"610\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2 itemprop=\"name\"><strong><span style=\"color:#16a085;\">International Middle Year Curriculum</span></strong></h2>\r\n</header>\r\n\r\n<section itemprop=\"articleBody\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">For students aged 11-14, students develop their knowledge, skills and understanding in Art, Geography, History, Science and Technology through the International Middle Years Curriculum (IMYC).</p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Students learn through five units during the course of each academic year. Each of these units is centered around a &#39;Big Idea&#39;, takes approximately six weeks to complete and culminates in a media presentation where children have the opportunity to showcase their learning to their family, peers and even the local community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The IMYC is a challenging, engaging, internationally-minded, and concept-focused curriculum. It is unique in that it addresses the question: What kind of people do we want our students to develop into? It is purposefully designed for the adolescent brain to help students make the transition from primary to secondary without becoming disengaged from their learning, to make meaning of their learning, to make connections with prior knowledge and to learn to take risks in an organised, safe and structured environment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>&ldquo;The IMYC is more than just a set of subject activities. It is a transformative and broad curriculum; it builds a culture and community focused on inspiring and engaging students, and supporting their learning needs. Learning happens everywhere, in school, at home and even on vacation as students take responsibility for their own learning.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n</section>', 3, 'middleyears/basketball-shot.jpg', 'default', 0, 'For students aged 11-14, students develop their knowledge, skills and understanding in Art, Geography, History, Science and Technology through the International Middle Years Curriculum (IMYC).', 'published', '2020-02-21 03:38:06', '2020-02-27 21:13:30'),
(52, 'Pathways to University', '<p><span style=\"color:#000000;\">As a Cambridge International Examination Centre, students are able to undertake Cambridge International Examinations at the end of each key stage.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Both the International Primary Curriculum and the International Middle Years Curriculum are designed to prepare students for further study wherever they are situated in the world, and enable international students to transition easily between schools and countries.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Following completion of the IMYC, students will possess the necessary knowledge, skills and understandings to undertake the International General Certificate of Secondary Education (IGCSE) and, later, the International Baccalaureate (IB), offering access to prestigious&nbsp;universities&nbsp;around the world.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; border:solid windowtext 1.0pt\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.8pt; border:solid windowtext 1.0pt\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#16a085;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">International Early Years Curriculum (IEYC)</span></span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.85pt; border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-left:none\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p align=\"center\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; text-align:center; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">Age 2-5</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.85pt; border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-left:none\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">The IEYC is built around four Learning Strands that underpin all learning and development:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">1 Independence and interdependence</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">2 Communicating</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">3 Enquiring</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">4 Healthy living and physical wellbeing</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.8pt; border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top:none\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#16a085;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\">International Primary Curriculum (IPC)</span></span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.85pt; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p align=\"center\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; text-align:center; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">Age 5-11</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.85pt; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">A broad and balanced curriculum, </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\"><span style=\"orphans:2; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\">including</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"float:none\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"> a combination of subject, personal and international learning.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.8pt; border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top:none\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#16a085;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">I</span></span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"float:none\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\">nternational </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\"><span style=\"orphans:2; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\">Middle</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"float:none\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"> Years Curriculum</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\"><span style=\"orphans:2; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"> (IMYC)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.85pt; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p align=\"center\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; text-align:center; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">Age 11-14</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.85pt; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">A challenging, internationally-minded and concept-focused curriculum, which helps develop engaged and active learners. With specific subject and personal learning goals, it provides a clear structure to develop knowledge, skills and understanding whilst making subject learning more connected.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.8pt; border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top:none\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#16a085;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\">International General Certificate of Secondary Education (IGCSE)</span></span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.85pt; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p align=\"center\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; text-align:center; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">Age 14-16</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.85pt; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">A wide choice of subjects at: Cambridge IGCSE </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\"><span style=\"orphans:2; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\">(70+ subjects)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.8pt; border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top:none\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#16a085;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">International Baccalaureate (IB) Diploma Programme (DP)</span></span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.85pt; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p align=\"center\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; text-align:center; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">Age 16-18</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:155.85pt; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt\" width=\"260\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span helvetica=\"\" neue=\"\">The programme aims to develop students who have excellent breadth and depth of knowledge &ndash; students who flourish physically, intellectually, emotionally and ethically. The curriculum is made up of six subject groups and the DP core, comprising theory of knowledge (TOK), creativity, activity, service (CAS) and the extended essay.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>', 3, 'primaryyears/library.jpg', 'default', 0, 'As a Cambridge International Examination Centre, students are able to undertake Cambridge International Examinations at the end of each key stage.', 'published', '2020-02-21 03:52:53', '2020-02-27 21:46:21'),
(53, 'Ages, Grades, Availability', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:11.25pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:25.0pt\"><span open=\"\" sans=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:#0082f3\">Ages, Grades, Availability</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:15.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:24.0pt\"><span open=\"\" sans=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:#0082f3\">2019/2020 Academic Year</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:11.25pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">This section is a guideline for parents to understand the class in which their children would be placed as different countries each have their own way of describing the school grades. Below is a comparison between the different countries to enable parents to understand our system more clearly. Please note that at Saigon Star we use the same terminology as schools in the UK.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:11.25pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">For the most up to date information regarding availability, please contact the Admissions Office on 02837423222 or 0888006996</span></span></span></p>', 3, 'primaryyears/hinhnen3.jpg', 'default', 0, 'This section is a guideline for parents to understand the class in which their children would be placed as different countries each have their own way of describing the school grades', 'published', '2020-02-21 05:00:50', '2020-02-25 03:43:25'),
(54, 'Admissions Process', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size:28px;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;\"><span style=\"color:#16a085;\">School Visits and Admissions Guidelines</span></span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">- If you would like to visit the school please pre-book a school tour by filling in the booking form in the Contact Us section or make an appointment by calling 0283742 3222 0r 08 8800 6996. You will receive a school tour as well as receive full information about our curriculum, provision and services. You will also have the opportunity to ask many questions.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">- Drop in parents will also receive a warm welcome but we would encourage you to please make an appointment if possible or you might have to wait a short while whilst we take parents around on pre-arranged tours.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">- You will be asked to fill in contact details for our record purposes only. If you think you would like your child/ren to join our school we will ask you to enroll and pay for your child/ren to have 2 days&rsquo; trail lessons, where they will be assessed for their ability and readiness for school. If the child is accepted, then this payment will be deducted from the tuition fees.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">- We will arrange a meeting with the Class Teacher and Head of School before the trial days for Early Years and Primary children and with the Head of School for Middle Years. If you are a parent of Early Years on Primary children, we will also ask you to supply the last progress from your child&rsquo;s school (where relevant) before the trial days go ahead. Parents of Middle Years children will be asked to supply the last 2 reports plus a letter of reference from your child/ren&rsquo;s last school.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">- Children from Year 2 upwards may use the school bus for the trial days but we would ask Mums, Dads and carers of Early Year, Primary and Year 1 students to please drop off and pick up your children. The teachers will guide you as to how long to stay in the classroom initially and you are very welcome to wait in one of our public areas.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">- Please bring your child/ren to the Admissions office at 8.30 am where they will be taken by a member of the team to the class teacher at 8.45 am. Depending on their age and individual needs mums, dads or carers may go with them too.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">- On Day 1 your child/ren will enjoy the classroom and class activities with his or her new friends. On Day 2 they will spend part of the day being assessed for English, Maths and aptitude. We will focus more on a child&rsquo;s potential than any current knowledge or skills so our parameters can be more flexible and broad than traditional testing.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">- After the trail days we will give you feedback from the 2 trial days. Following a successful recommendation, and if you decide to go ahead, you may ask for a fee quotation at any time. You will be required to pay a deposit and your child may start 2 weeks after the enrolment has been processed and full payment has been made. The 2-week period is for the teacher to prepare and organize extra resources in readiness for your child.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">- Prior to starting school, you will also be asked to produce the required documents, such as the student&rsquo;s passport, and birth certificate, medical history book and 2 passport size photos.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">- Once the fees have been paid the student will be given 2 sets of the formal uniform, one sports kit and one school cap.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">-&nbsp; Admissions will send a letter of confirmation after full payment has been made.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px;\">- We look forward to welcoming you and your child/ren to our school and hope that they will be with us for many happy years to come.</span></span></p>', 3, NULL, 'default', 0, 'Admissions Policy as from March 2020\r\n- Parents are encouraged to pre-book a school tour but drop in parents are\r\nalso welcomed.', 'published', '2020-03-02 03:40:44', '2020-03-02 23:48:37');
